<br>
Both of them take the mastery of your class to play, not every wizard can do them.  You'd be suprised just how many wizards don't quad kite, and how few dare to step in the midst of 40 mobs and hold it together.<br>
<br>
The risk vs. reward factor is high, anything can go wrong, and exp can quickly be lost, thereby emptying the cash flow to regain it.  This cash flow, meanwhile, isn't quite as high as I would imagine the average melee gains for this reason:  The cost of any given piece of equipment for a melee is signifigantly higher and changed more often than a caster.  You get a robe, you wear it for 5-20 levels sometimes.  The graphics underneath aren't shown, and you find the best int or mana items with resists you can, then rarely upgrade them.  Armor is available in all shapes and sizes, with different looks, in full suits.  It drops more frequently as I feel there is more of it out there, and more often than not you won't see a caster walking away with the nice melee BP when there's a melee present.<br>
<br>
Quad kiting is our means to experience.  AE groups are our means to get melee loot in all caster groups.  I feel that's balance.  Maybe I went off on a tagent, as I always do, but there it is. <p><center><img src="http://members.home.net/erichuinker/signature1.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukazzapkaboom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazzap Kaboom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/25/01 11:48:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards have it Easy</span><hr size=1> that pisses me off cause i <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  CANT </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> quad well... <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  YET </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> i think i could if DL wasnt so camped or i had Velious <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
